"'''The Second Kessel Run'''" is a [[Star Wars (comic strip)|comic strip]] that was distributed by the [[Los Angeles Times Syndicate]] and published in U.S. and Canadian newspapers. This story was written by [[Russ Helm]] and drawn by [[Russ Manning]]. It was collected in [[Classic Star Wars: The Early Adventures 6|''Classic Star Wars: The Early Adventures'' 6]], and was also available in the [[Star Wars comic books|Webstrips]] section of [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]].

==Plot summary==
Above the planet [[Zerm/Legends|Zerm]], [[Professor/Legends|Professor]] [[Renn Volz]] tests his ''[[Ionic Ring Ship]]''. The test proves successful, and the weather on Zerm changes and killer storms stop. Volz then plans on using the ''Ionic Ring'' on [[Little Kessel/Legends|Kessel]]. However, before he can do this, [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Bzorn]] arrives on board Volz's ship and takes the professor's daughter, [[Mira Volz]], hostage. Bzorn plans to use the ''Ionic Ring'' to devastate [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] planets. He threatens the professor, telling Volz that if the professor won't obey him, Bzorn will kill his daughter.

On a distant spaceport, Mira manages to escape from the [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] who were guarding her and sneak into the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']], which was being loading with [[Spice/Legends|spice]]. [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] are going to make another [[Kessel Run/Legends|Kessel Run]] for [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba the Hutt]], but first he was going to pick up [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]]. On the hidden Rebel base on the planet [[Randa/Legends|Randa]], Han picks up Luke, [[R2-D2/Legends|Artoo]] and [[C-3PO/Legends|Threepio]] and finds his unexpected guest. Mira tells Luke and Han about Bzorn's plan and asks Han to deliver her to the professor, knowing that he will stop the destruction after he learns that Mira is safe.

Meanwhile, the ''Ionic Ring'' turns the rebel planet [[Rion/Legends|Rion]] from a tropical paradise to a snowy desert. After arriving on Rion, Han gives some of his spice to the refugees who are starving. One refugee turns Mira over to the stormtroopers for food, but with the help of the other Rebels, she manages to escape. During her escape she learns that Bzorn's next target is going to be Kessel, her home planet. The ''Millennium Falcon'' manages to arrive on Kessel before the ''Ionic Ring'', setting another new record for the Kessel Run.

Mira uses her father's [[sub-space image transmitter]] to project her image on the ''Ionic Ring'', which has already arrived in the system and has started an earthquake. Han suggests trying something else and they board the ship in the guise of surrendered Rebels. Mira's floating image creates enough distractions for the stormtroopers to allow Han and Luke to get to the command center. After Volz sees the image of his daughter, Bzorn orders the stormtroopers to kill everyone, but he is soon hit by friendly fire. Professor Volz, fearing that the Empire won't stop until it obtains his creation again, commences the ship's self-destruction and barely escapes with Luke, Han and Chewbacca on the ''Millennium Falcon''.

==Continuity==
Han Solo states that he is making the Kessel Run for Jabba the Hutt. This means that the events depicted in the comic happened between [[Marvel Comics|Marvel]] [[Star Wars (1977) 28|''Star Wars'' (1977) 28]] and [[Star Wars (1977) 37|''Star Wars'' (1977) 37]], in a period when Jabba forgave Solo's debt.

[[Kessel/Legends|Kessel]], as depicted in this series, was a lush, idyllic world containing the [[Giant Fungi Forest]]. According to ''[[The Essential Atlas]]'', and confirmed by [[Jason Fry]] on the [[Jedi Council Forums]], this depiction has been [[Retroactive continuity|retconned]] into being [[Little Kessel/Legends|Little Kessel]], a world not far off the Kessel Run.<ref name="Jason Fry Little Kessel">{{JCFCite|url=posts/30364686|board=Literature|thread=The Essential Atlas and Galactic Cartography: Official Discussion|user=[[Jason Fry|jasonfry]]|date=2009-08-20|time=5:45 AM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171212045150/http://boards.theforce.net/threads/the-essential-atlas-and-galactic-cartography-official-discussion.21938930/page-90|quote=Yes. A bit of a "Hoth Stuff" style retcon, perhaps, but I thought it worked OK.}}</ref>

